item.description:
==Characteristics &amp; Trends== Indian Agriculture is primarily characterized as a Subsistence Sector [Jivan Nirvah Kshetra], where the primary goal of the farmer is to sustain the household rather than purely commercial profit. It is a Labor-Intensive sector that contributes approximately 18-19% to the Gross Value Added (GVA) while employing nearly 45% of the workforce.
tax on income- income tax.. (&ndash;other than agri. income) &mdash;
2. The Mechanism The functioning of Indian agriculture follows a complex cycle heavily influenced by climatic and structural factors.
